1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Anthony
2 "Tony" McCoart.
3 WHEREAS, Anthony "Tony" McCoart was born on February 28, 1955, in Johnson
4 County, Kentucky, to the late Bessie and Art McCoart; and
5 WHEREAS, Tony McCoart loved to play golf and support the Van Lear Historical
6 Society; and
7 WHEREAS, Tony McCoart was a vibrant, lively, and loyal husband, father,
8 grandfather, brother, friend, teammate, coworker, and neighbor; and
9 WHEREAS, after a hard-fought battle with corticobasal degeneration, Tony
10 McCoart departed this earthly life on March 15, 2025. He joins his parents and brothers,
11 Henry, Frank "Burns," and Dan, in eternal life; and
12 WHEREAS, Tony McCoart will be forever remembered and deeply missed by his
13 devoted wife of 48 years, Teresa McCoart; his two daughters, Jennifer (Derrick) Wilson
14 and Lauren McCoart; his two grandchildren, Lily and Sawyer; his twin sister, Angie
15 (Harold) Burton; his sisters, Jenny (Bill) Phelps and Patty Lee; and his brother, John Pat
16 McCoart;
17 NOW, THEREFORE,
18 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
19 Kentucky:
20 Section 1. The members of the Senate hereby express their most profound
21 sympathy upon the passing of Tony McCoart.
22 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor and loving
23 memory of Tony McCoart.
24 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
25 Resolution to Senator Phillip Wheeler for delivery to the family.
